contentMeta.description: All sports concepts in one G2 knowledge doc

concept.name: rank
rank
concept.definition: How this player ranks among the other competing players.

concept.name: handicap
handicap
concept.definition: The handicap-value of this player. This will normally not be used in professional tournaments.

concept.name: rounds
rounds
concept.definition: How many rounds the player or team has completed in this particular tournament.

concept.name: average
average
concept.definition: Average score of the player or team. Number of shots devided by number of holes??

concept.name: distance-longest
distance-longest
concept.definition: The longest distance the player shot.

concept.name: distance-rank
distance-rank
concept.definition: The rank in the round or tournament for the player when comparing the longest distance shot.

concept.name: drives
drives
concept.definition: The number of drives made by the player.

concept.name: total-rounds
total-rounds
concept.definition: Total number of rounds played during the current tournament.

concept.name: total-strokes
total-strokes
concept.definition: Total number of strokes (or swings) (or shots) made.

concept.name: total-holes
total-holes
concept.definition: Total number of holes played.

concept.name: total-putts
total-putts
concept.definition: Total number of putts attempted.

concept.name: total-points
total-points
concept.definition: Total score of the player. Depending on the system used in the tournament the score could be something other than the actual number of strokes.

concept.name: total-driving
total-driving
concept.definition: Total driving distance.

concept.name: total-par-or-less
total-par-or-less
concept.definition: Total number of holes played by the player at par or less than par.

concept.name: birdies
birdies
concept.definition: Number of birdies.

concept.name: birdies-rank
birdies-rank
concept.definition: How the player ranks in the round or tournament regarding birdies.

concept.name: eagles
eagles
concept.definition: Number of eagles.

concept.name: eagles-rank
eagles-rank
concept.definition: How the player ranks in the round or tournament regarding eagles.

concept.name: saves
saves
concept.definition: Number of saves when the ball landed in a sand bunker.

concept.name: saves-rank
saves-rank
concept.definition: How the player ranks in the round or tournament regarding saves from the bunker.

concept.name: bunkers
bunkers
concept.definition: Number of bunker shots the player took.

concept.name: eagle-per-holes-frequency
eagle-per-holes-frequency
concept.definition: Frequency of hitting eagles.

concept.name: greens-hit
greens-hit
concept.definition: This is a very special golf term. To reach a green in regulation (GIR) the player must place the ball on the green with two strokes less than the par of the course. The attribute holds the number of times the player or team has achieved this in the timeframe the stats cover.

concept.name: greens-hit-rank
greens-hit-rank
concept.definition: How the player ranks in the tournament or round regarding greens hit in regulation.

concept.name: greens-in-regulation-missed
greens-in-regulation-missed
concept.definition: Number of greens missed during regulation play.

concept.name: greens-in-regulation-putting
greens-in-regulation-putting
concept.definition: The average number of puts needed to finish holes after hitting the green in regulation (GIR).

concept.name: greens-in-regulation-rank
greens-in-regulation-rank
concept.definition: Rank of player in terms of the greens-in-regulation putting.

concept.name: fairways-hit
fairways-hit
concept.definition: Number of fairways hit.

concept.name: fairways-possible
fairways-possible
concept.definition: Maximum number of fairways it was possible to hit.

concept.name: putts-per-round
putts-per-round
concept.definition: The average number of putts needed per complete round.

concept.name: putts-per-round-rank
putts-per-round-rank
concept.definition: How the player ranks when comparing the average putts-per-round.

concept.name: holes-under-par
holes-under-par
concept.definition: Number of holes finished under par.

concept.name: scoring-adjustment
scoring-adjustment
concept.definition: Scoring adjustment.

concept.name: finishes-top-10
finishes-top-10
concept.definition: Number of finishes the player had in the top ten.

concept.name: finishes-first-place
finishes-first-place
concept.definition: Number of first-place finishes the player had.

concept.name: finishes-second-place
finishes-second-place
concept.definition: Number of second-place finishes the player had.

concept.name: performance-par-3
performance-par-3
concept.definition: The performance of the player on par-3 holes.

concept.name: performance-par-4
performance-par-4
concept.definition: The performance of the player on par-4 holes.

concept.name: performance-par-5
performance-par-5
concept.definition: The performance of the player on par-5 holes.

concept.name: money
money
concept.definition: Amount of money earned by the player.

concept.name: money-value
money-value
concept.definition: Money value.

concept.name: points
points
concept.definition: Number of points.

concept.name: points-lost
points-lost
concept.definition: Number of points lost.

concept.name: points-gained
points-gained
concept.definition: Number of points gained.

concept.name: drive-accuracy
drive-accuracy
concept.definition: A percentage of how good the drives from the player or team has been in the given frame the stats cover.

concept.name: drive-accuracy-rank
drive-accuracy-rank
concept.definition: How the player ranks when comparing drive-accuracy.

concept.name: rounds-under-par
rounds-under-par
concept.definition: The number of rounds the player has completed a course under par.

concept.name: bogeys
bogeys
concept.definition: The number of holes finished one above par for that hole.

concept.name: bogeys-rank
bogeys-rank
concept.definition: How the player ranks when comparing bogeys.

concept.name: double-bogeys
double-bogeys
concept.definition: The number of holes finished two above par for that hole.

concept.name: double-bogeys-rank
double-bogeys-rank
concept.definition: How the player ranks when comparing double-bogeys.

concept.name: finish-other
finish-other
concept.definition: The number of holes finished with either more than two under par or two over par.

concept.name: finish-other-rank
finish-other-rank
concept.definition: How the player ranks when comparing finish-other.

concept.name: pars
pars
concept.definition: The number of holes finished on par.

concept.name: pars-rank
pars-rank
concept.definition: How the player ranks when comparing pars.

concept.name: speed-average-race
speed-average-race
concept.definition: The average speed of the race.

concept.name: lead-changes
lead-changes
concept.definition: The number of times the lead changed in this race.

concept.name: lead-changes-drivers
lead-changes-drivers
concept.definition: Total number of drivers that comprised the lead changes.

concept.name: margin-of-victory
margin-of-victory
concept.definition: Time behind leader for 2nd place driver.

concept.name: caution-flags
caution-flags
concept.definition: Total number of flags for race.

concept.name: caution-flags-laps
caution-flags-laps
concept.definition: Total number of laps there were caution flags.

concept.name: laps-total
laps-total
concept.definition: Total number of laps for race.

concept.name: distance-lap
distance-lap
concept.definition: Length of one lap.

concept.name: distance-total
distance-total
concept.definition: Total distance of race.

concept.name: grid
grid
concept.definition: The arrangement or order of cars in the starting lineup.

concept.name: pole-position
pole-position
concept.definition: Position relative to the inside wall, at the start of the race.

concept.name: pole-wins
pole-wins
concept.definition: Number of times this driver or team had a pole position of 1.

concept.name: qualifying-speed
qualifying-speed
concept.definition: Speed of lap which qualified the driver.

concept.name: qualifying-time
qualifying-time
concept.definition: Time received for qualifying lap.

concept.name: qualifying-position
qualifying-position
concept.definition: Where the car had ranked within the preliminary round.

concept.name: time-behind-leader
time-behind-leader
concept.definition: Amount of time this driver was behind the car that is currently in first place.

concept.name: laps-behind-leader
laps-behind-leader
concept.definition: Amount of laps this driver was behind the car that is currently in first place.

concept.name: time-ahead-follower
time-ahead-follower
concept.definition: Amount of time this driver was ahead of the car immediately behind it.

concept.name: laps-ahead-follower
laps-ahead-follower
concept.definition: Amount of laps this driver was ahead of the car immediately behind it.

concept.name: time
time
concept.definition: Total amount of time this driver has been competing in the race.

concept.name: points
points
concept.definition: Total accumulation of points in the league-authorized standings for the season.

concept.name: points-rookie
points-rookie
concept.definition: Total accumulation of points in the league-authorized standings for the season, amongst other drivers who are competing in their first year.

concept.name: bonus
bonus
concept.definition: Amount of bonus points driver has earned in this race. For example, NASCAR drivers may receive five bonus points for leading a lap, and an additional five points for leading the most laps.

concept.name: laps-completed
laps-completed
concept.definition: Number of laps this driver has completed during this race.

concept.name: laps-leading-total
laps-leading-total
concept.definition: Number of laps in which this driver has led the field.

concept.name: distance-leading
distance-leading
concept.definition: Distance (in, say, miles or kilometers) that driver has led the race.

concept.name: distance-completed
distance-completed
concept.definition: Distance (in, say, miles or kilometers) that driver has completed in this race.

concept.name: speed-average
speed-average
concept.definition: Average speed during the race.

concept.name: status
status
concept.definition: Whether the driver is running, or is out of the race.

concept.name: finishes-top-5
finishes-top-5
concept.definition: Number of top-5 finishes this driver has had.

concept.name: finishes-top-10
finishes-top-10
concept.definition: Number of top-10 finishes this driver has had.

concept.name: starts
starts
concept.definition: Number of races this driver had started.

concept.name: finishes
finishes
concept.definition: Number of races this driver had finished.

concept.name: non-finishes
non-finishes
concept.definition: Number of races this driver had started but had not finished.

concept.name: wins
wins
concept.definition: Number of races this driver had won.

concept.name: races-leading
races-leading
concept.definition: Number of races in which this driver has held a lead.

concept.name: money
money
concept.definition: Amount of money this driver had won.

concept.name: leads-total
leads-total
concept.definition: Number of total leads this driver has had, presumably during this race.

concept.name: comment
comment
concept.definition: A comment or highlight on this driver.

concept.name: speed-range
speed-range
concept.definition: Either fastest or slowest.

concept.name: lap-number
lap-number
concept.definition: The lap number in question.

concept.name: start-time-elapsed
start-time-elapsed
concept.definition: The time since the start of the race at which this lap was begun.

concept.name: speed-average-lap
speed-average-lap
concept.definition: The average speed of this lap.

concept.name: duration
duration
concept.definition: The length of time this lap (or partial lap) was completed.

concept.name: split-location
split-location
concept.definition: Used when partial laps are being timed. If omitted, it is assumed that the stats herein are for the entire lap. Sample values include: start | stretch | finish | marker-1 | marker-2

concept.name: hosted
hosted
concept.definition: For a tournament that holds stages in different locations. Eg. different host cities/countries for PGA, FIS, Diamond League (IAAF) and even Tour de France

concept.name: single-group
single-group
concept.definition: The stage involves only a single group of competitors. For example Italian Serie A where teams vie for placement in the league table. Also, a single group competition in a multi-group stage, such as the World Cup group stage.

concept.name: series
series
concept.definition: A stage in which two competitors face off in a series of games (eg. best 3 of 5) the winner of which proceeds to the next stage, or wins the tournament.

concept.name: single-elimination
single-elimination
concept.definition: A stage in which two competitors face off in a single match to determine who proceeds to the next stage, or wins the tournament. Eg. elimination stage of World Cup of Soccer or NFL playoffs.

concept.name: home-and-home
home-and-home
concept.definition: A stage in which two competitors face off in a two matches (or legs) at each team's home location. The overall winner proceeds ahead. Usually culiminates in a single-elimination match at a neutral location i.e. UEFA Champions League.

concept.name: wins
wins
concept.definition: Number of wins.

concept.name: losses
losses
concept.definition: Number of losses.

concept.name: ties
ties
concept.definition: Number of ties.

concept.name: undecideds
undecideds
concept.definition: Number of events that were started, but ended up undecided.

concept.name: winning-percentage
winning-percentage
concept.definition: The winning percentage. Generally, wins divided by total events completed.

concept.name: points-scored-for
points-scored-for
concept.definition: The number of points a team has scored against its opponents during an extended time period.

concept.name: points-scored-against
points-scored-against
concept.definition: The number of points scored against a team by its opponents during an extended time period.

concept.name: points-difference
points-difference
concept.definition: The final calculated difference between points-scored-for and points-scored-against. Possibly takes into account other scoring aspects, such as penalties and differences in score-values.

concept.name: standing-points
standing-points
concept.definition: A quantity used to rank teams, usually within a division, in order to decide who comes in first at the end of a season. Localized to the coverage-attributes.

concept.name: standing-points-against
standing-points-against
concept.definition: Points counted against a team in rankings. Used in European handball standings, for example.

concept.name: streak-duration
streak-duration
concept.definition: How long the streak lasted.

concept.name: streak-total
streak-total
concept.definition: Holds the number of goals scored during a streak-type of score, for example.

concept.name: streak-start
streak-start
concept.definition: Date on which the streak began.

concept.name: streak-end
streak-end
concept.definition: Date on which the streak ended.

concept.name: events-discarded
events-discarded
concept.definition: The number of events that the team or player has discarded under this particular time period. Added from issue #29 2019-03-20.

concept.name: games-back
games-back
concept.definition: A number used to measure how behind one team is from first place. The first place team is 0 games back.

concept.name: losses-overtime
losses-overtime
concept.definition: Number of losses in events which went into overtime. For leagues that use this as a top-level outcome category (eg. NHL), as opposed to just a derivative of scoping.

concept.name: relegation-average
relegation-average
concept.definition: The product of a relegation average formula used to determine which team is demoted to a lower league. The formula may vary by league but the average typically looks at team performance across multiple competitions. The team(s) with the lowest relegation averages is sent to the league below.

concept.name: points
points
concept.definition: Points accumulated by this associate. For example, points earned by a NASCAR owner.

concept.name: events-played
events-played
concept.definition: The number of sports-events in which this team or player has already participated.

concept.name: time-played-total
time-played-total
concept.definition: Value for the amount of time played by the team or player over the course of a particular time-span, such as a season.

concept.name: time-played-event
time-played-event
concept.definition: Value for the amount of time played by this player in a particular sports-event.

concept.name: time-played-event-average
time-played-event-average
concept.definition: Value for the average amount of time played per-event by the player over the course of a particular time-span, such as a season.

concept.name: events-started
events-started
concept.definition: Number of sports-events the player has played in since the start of the event.

concept.name: period-extra-time-added
period-extra-time-added
concept.definition: How many minutes the referee has decided to add to the period.

concept.name: period-extra-time-elapsed
period-extra-time-elapsed
concept.definition: How much time exactly MMSS that was actually elapsed in the period.

concept.name: score
score
concept.definition: Final or current score of the team or player.

concept.name: score-opposing
score-opposing
concept.definition: Final or current score of the opposing team or player.

concept.name: score-average
score-average
concept.definition: Average per-game score for the team or player.

concept.name: score-opposing-average
score-opposing-average
concept.definition: Average per-game score for the opposing team or player.

concept.name: score-behind
score-behind
concept.definition: The points or time behind the leading score.

concept.name: score-attempts
score-attempts
concept.definition: Final or current number of attempts to score by a team or player. Example: in ice hockey, would represent total shots on goal.

concept.name: score-attempts-opposing
score-attempts-opposing
concept.definition: Final or current number of attempts to score by an opposing team or player.

concept.name: score-attempts-on-goal
score-attempts-on-goal
concept.definition: A subset of score-attempts. Only counts those attempts that were on-goal.

concept.name: score-attempts-on-goal-opposing
score-attempts-on-goal-opposing
concept.definition: Final or current number of attempts to score by an opposing team or player that were on-goal.

concept.name: score-percentage
score-percentage
concept.definition: Percentage of attempted scores that reached their mark.

concept.name: score-percentage-opposing
score-percentage-opposing
concept.definition: Percentage of attempted scores by opposing team or player that reached their mark.

concept.name: result-effect
result-effect
concept.definition: Describes the effect that the result of the event or rank changing has had on the team. Example: Whether or not a team has qualified for the playoffs, or has been promoted or demoted to a different division.

concept.name: event-outcome
event-outcome
concept.definition: Whether the competitor won, lost, or tied.

concept.name: event-standing-points
event-standing-points
concept.definition: How many points were earned as a result of the outcome of this particular event.

concept.name: event-standing-points-against
event-standing-points-against
concept.definition: How many points were deducted as a result of the outcome of this particular event. This occurs, for example, in the German Handball leagues.

concept.name: events-remaining
events-remaining
concept.definition: Number of sports-events the player has yet to participate in.

concept.name: time-of-possession
time-of-possession
concept.definition: Amount of time the team or player has possession of ball (or similar object like puck).

concept.name: time-of-possession-percentage
time-of-possession-percentage
concept.definition: Amount of time the team or player has possession of ball (or similar object like puck) expressed as a percentage of the full time of the match.

concept.name: time-of-possession-percentage-opposing
time-of-possession-percentage-opposing
concept.definition: Amount of time the opposing team or player has possession of ball (or similar object like puck) expressed as a percentage of the full time of the match.

concept.name: time-of-possession-average
time-of-possession-average
concept.definition: Amount of time the team or player has possession of ball (or similar object like puck) per game.

concept.name: time-of-possession-average-opposing
time-of-possession-average-opposing
concept.definition: Amount of time the opposing team or player has possession of ball (or similar object like puck) per game.

concept.name: series-score
series-score
concept.definition: Number of events in a series won by team or player.

concept.name: series-score-opposing
series-score-opposing
concept.definition: Number of events in a series won by opposing team or player.

concept.name: adjusted-score-for
adjusted-score-for
concept.definition: The final score as adjusted by some authority. Usually as a result of some dispute or transgression that must be settled post-event and rendered in the score. Will differ from the regular score reflecting the number of actual goals scored in play. Should be tested for before displaying actual score.

concept.name: adjusted-score-against
adjusted-score-against
concept.definition: The final score against as adjusted by some authority. Usually as a result of some dispute or transgression that must be settled post-event and rendered in the score. Will differ from the regular score reflecting the number of actual goals scored in play. Should be tested for before displaying actual score.

concept.name: withdrawal
withdrawal
concept.definition: A forfeited or canceled event because a participant withdrew.

concept.name: time-absolute
time-absolute
concept.definition: Total time to complete competition, not measured in comparison to other competitors

concept.name: time-relative
time-relative
concept.definition: Time difference compared (usually) to closest competitor or first-place finalist. First place commonly has absolute value.

concept.name: season-type
season-type
concept.definition: Which segment of the season: pre-season, post-season, regular, etc.

concept.name: Regular Season
Regular Season
concept.definition: The phase of a season during which competitors vie for placement in a playoff phase.

concept.name: Post Season
Post Season
concept.definition: The phase of a season after the regular season during which competitors vie for the league championship.

concept.name: Pre Season
Pre Season
concept.definition: The phase of a season during which exhibition matches are played.

concept.name: News
News
concept.definition: A category of sports documents: non-event-specific news reports for player, team, league, etc.

concept.name: Standings
Standings
concept.definition: A category of sports documents: often also called "tables"

concept.name: Schedules
Schedules
concept.definition: A category of sports documents.

concept.name: Statistics
Statistics
concept.definition: A category of sports documents: for non-event-specific statistical reports

concept.name: Event Summary
Event Summary
concept.definition: A category of sports documents: for event-specific reports whether prose (i.e. previews and reviews) or statistical (i.e. boxscores))

concept.name: Event Action
Event Action
concept.definition: A category of sports documents: for play actions within a single event

concept.name: Dynamic Resource File
Dynamic Resource File
concept.definition: A category of sports documents: for team rosters (squad lists), athlete lists, league groupings and teams, etc.

concept.name: Statistic
Statistic
concept.definition: A statistical indicator of on-field performance in sport.

concept.name: Core
Core
concept.definition: A class of position, role or statistic in sport.

concept.name: Offense
Offense
concept.definition: A class of position, role or statistic in sport.

concept.name: Defense
Defense
concept.definition: A class of position, role or statistic in sport.

concept.name: Special Teams
Special Teams
concept.definition: A class of role or statistic in (usually) American Football.

concept.name: Fumbles
Fumbles
concept.definition: A class of role or statistic in American Football.

concept.name: Penalties
Penalties
concept.definition: A class of role or statistic in American Football.

concept.name: Face-offs
Face-offs
concept.definition: A class of statistic in Ice Hockey.

concept.name: Time On Ice
Time On Ice
concept.definition: A class of statistic in Ice Hockey.

concept.name: Pitching
Pitching
concept.definition: A class of statistic in Baseball.

concept.name: Rebounding
Rebounding
concept.definition: A class of statistic in Basketball.

concept.name: Scoring
Scoring
concept.definition: A class of statistic in sport.

concept.name: publisher
publisher
concept.definition: The source of the data/content.

concept.name: distributor
distributor
concept.definition: The immediate provider of the data/content.

concept.name: single-team
single-team
concept.definition: Contains only information about a single team.

concept.name: multi-team
multi-team
concept.definition: Contains information about many or all teams in a league.

concept.name: qualification
qualification
concept.definition: The stage, usually prior to a group or elimination stage, where entities compete to qualify for the later "playoff" stage.

concept.name: single-point
single-point
concept.definition: In Canadian football, a single point is awarded when a kick landing in the end zone cannot be returned.

concept.name: yards-per-attempt
yards-per-attempt
concept.definition: The average yards gained per play.

concept.name: number-of-plays
number-of-plays
concept.definition: The number of plays this team has completed, including for offensive, defensive, and special teams.

concept.name: number-of-plays-gaining
number-of-plays-gaining
concept.definition: The number of plays this team has completed for which yards were gained, including for offensive, defensive, and special teams.

concept.name: number-of-plays-losing
number-of-plays-losing
concept.definition: The number of plays this team has completed for which yards were lost, including for offensive, defensive, and special teams.

concept.name: average-starting-position
average-starting-position
concept.definition: Average yard-line that the team started on per-drive.

concept.name: timeouts
timeouts
concept.definition: The number of timeouts a team has remaining, either in regulation or in overtime, whichever state the game is currently in.

concept.name: turnover-ratio
turnover-ratio
concept.definition: Derived by subtracting turnovers-giveaways from turnovers-takeaways.

concept.name: offensive-plays-yards
offensive-plays-yards
concept.definition: The total yards accumulated through offensive plays.

concept.name: offensive-plays-number
offensive-plays-number
concept.definition: The number of offensive plays.

concept.name: offensive-plays-average-yards-per
offensive-plays-average-yards-per
concept.definition: The average number of yards gained per play.

concept.name: offensive-plays-average-yards-per-game
offensive-plays-average-yards-per-game
concept.definition: The average number of yards gained via offensive plays per game.

concept.name: offensive-rank
offensive-rank
concept.definition: How team's offense compares with rest of league or conference.

concept.name: possession-duration
possession-duration
concept.definition: The average amount of time the team had possession per-drive.

concept.name: possessions-inside-20
possessions-inside-20
concept.definition: Number of times team has driven inside its opponent's 20 yard line.

concept.name: turnovers-giveaway
turnovers-giveaway
concept.definition: Derived by adding passes-interceptions plus fumbles-own-lost.

concept.name: turnovers-giveaway-average
turnovers-giveaway-average
concept.definition: Average-per-game for turnovers-giveaway.

concept.name: handoffs-total
handoffs-total
concept.definition: Usually, number of times QB has handed off, typically leading to a running play.

concept.name: pitches-total
pitches-total
concept.definition: Usually, number of times QB has pitched back to another player, typically leading to a running play.

concept.name: tackles-offense
tackles-offense
concept.definition: The number of tackles performed while on offense.

concept.name: tackles-assists-offense
tackles-assists-offense
concept.definition: The number of tackle assists performed while on offense.

concept.name: passes-attempts
passes-attempts
concept.definition: The number of passes attempted.

concept.name: passes-completions
passes-completions
concept.definition: The number of passes completed successfully.

concept.name: passes-completions-average-per-game
passes-completions-average-per-game
concept.definition: Average number of completed passes a game.

concept.name: passes-percentage
passes-percentage
concept.definition: The percentage of all passes that are completed successfully.

concept.name: passes-yards-gross
passes-yards-gross
concept.definition: The number of yards gained from passing.

concept.name: passes-yards-net
passes-yards-net
concept.definition: Subtracts out the sacks-against-yards-lost value of stats-american-football-sacks-against element.

concept.name: passes-yards-lost
passes-yards-lost
concept.definition: Amount of yards lost due to sacks and completed passing plays that ended behind the line of scrimmage.

concept.name: passes-yards-per-attempt
passes-yards-per-attempt
concept.definition: Gross passing yards divided by number of pass attempts.

concept.name: passes-first-down
passes-first-down
concept.definition: Number of passes a player or team has made for a first-down.

concept.name: passes-touchdowns-percentage

concept.name: draw
draw
concept.definition: A shot trying to place the stone inside the house.

concept.name: come-around

concept.definition: A shot trying to move the stone around another stone placing the new stone inside the house.

concept.name: front
front
concept.definition: A shot with the intention of placing the stone in front of the house.

concept.name: guard
guard
concept.definition: A shot that is placed in front of another stone to protect it from being knocked out by the other team, or placed with the intent to later curl another rock around it and thus be protected; typically placed between the hog line and the very front of the house.

concept.name: raise
raise
concept.definition: Using one stone to hit another stone with the intention of moving it forward.

concept.name: freeze
freeze
concept.definition: A precise draw weight shot where a delivered stone comes to rest against a stationary stone, making it nearly impossible to knock out.

concept.name: split
split
concept.definition: A draw shot in which the played stone hits on the side of a stationary stone and both move sideways and stay in play.

concept.name: tick
tick
concept.definition: A shot that bumps a guard out of the way without removing it from play.

concept.name: takeout
takeout
concept.definition: A shot that tries to hit and remove another stone from the game.

concept.name: hit-and-roll
hit-and-roll
concept.definition: A shot that tries to hit and remove another stone from the game and then moving the shot stone sideways.

concept.name: clearing
clearing
concept.definition: A shot that tries to hit and remove (an)other stone(s) including the shot stone.

concept.name: double
double
concept.definition: A shot that tries to hit and remove two other stones.

concept.name: raise-takeout
raise-takeout
concept.definition: A shot that tries to hit another stone that in turn should hit a third stone removing that stone from play.

concept.name: not-considered
not-considered
concept.definition: A shot that is not to be considered in the statistics for the game.

concept.name: team-fault
team-fault
concept.definition: A shot that the team made something wrong with like touching the stone after release etc.

concept.name: blank
blank
concept.definition: A stone that is not played at all, for example all remaining stones in the game when one team has given up the game.

concept.name: A
A
concept.definition: The player is a reserve for the team.
The player plays the first stones for the team. In a four player team the player plays stones 1 and 2. If the team only has three players the first player plays stones 1-3.
The player plays second for the team, stones 3 and 4 when the team has four players, stones 4-6 if a three player team.
The player plays third for the team, stones 5 and 6 if the team has four players, the last two stones if a three player team.
The player plays the last two stones if the team has four players.
